            <title>[LU-8844] Delete llite lloop with fire!!!</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8844</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the migration of lustre to clio the llite lloop driver&apos;s performance advantage over the standard loop back driver disappeared. Also lloop never functioned on non-x86 platforms. With new kernels (4.5+) loop back devices supporting directIO it make even more of a case to delete llite lloop driver.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
